<%= form_for @bal_quiz do |f| %>
  <div class="row">
      <div class="row buffer-25"></div>

      <div class="container col-xs-10 col-xs-push-1 quiz-question">
        <div class="form-group">
          <h3>Q1: Forward Foot Balance</h3>
          <p><strong>How to Perform Stand on Forward Leg</strong>
            <ol>
              <li>Look straight ahead. Keep your hands on your hips.</li>
              <li>Check the second hand on your watch as you lift your back leg off of the ground without touching or resting your raised leg upon your other standing leg. </li>
              <li>Stay standing on one leg as long as you can, looking straight ahead.</li>
              <li>When you lose balance, check how many seconds passed.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <div class="radio left-padding-30">
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '7'%><label>0 - 5 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '6'%><label>6 - 9 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '5'%><label>10 - 15 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '4'%><label>16 - 20 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '3'%><label>21 - 25 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '2'%><label>26 - 30 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal01, '1'%><label>31 Seconds or More</label>
          </div> <!-- radio buttons -->
        </div> <!-- form group -->
      </div> <!-- opaque container -->

      <div class="container col-xs-10 col-xs-push-1 quiz-question">
        <div class="form-group">
          <h3>Q2: Forward Foot Balance, Motion</h3>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>Take your golf posture with arms in front.</li>
              <li>Lift your back leg off of the ground without touching or resting your raised leg upon your other standing leg.</li>
              <li>Check the second hand on your watch once your leg is raised.</li>
              <li>Now slowly turn your forward arm in and let your hips turn, then slowly return back to your original position</li>
              <li>Do this several times stay standing on one leg as long as you can, looking straight ahead.</li>
              <li>When you lose balance, check how many seconds have passed.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <div class="radio left-padding-30">
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '7'%><label>0 - 5 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '6'%><label>6 - 9 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '5'%><label>10 - 15 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '4'%><label>16 - 20 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '3'%><label>21 - 25 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '2'%><label>26 - 30 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal02, '1'%><label>31 Seconds or More</label>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> <!-- opaque container -->

      <div class="container col-xs-10 col-xs-push-1 quiz-question">
        <div class="form-group">
          <h3>Q3: Forward Foot Balance, Eyes Closed</h3>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>Stand tall with your arms down by you side, but not touching their sides</li>
              <li>Elevate back leg until the thigh is parallel with the ground.</li>
              <li>Once stable look at the second hand on your watch, then close your eyes and see how long you can maintain balance. Any re-positioning of the foot is considered a loss of balance.</li>
              <li>When you lose balance, open your eyes and see how many seconds passed.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <div class="radio left-padding-30">
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '7'%><label>0 - 5 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '6'%><label>6 - 9 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '5'%><label>10 - 15 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '4'%><label>16 - 20 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '3'%><label>21 - 25 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '2'%><label>26 - 30 Seconds</label><br>
            <%= f.radio_button :bal03, '1'%><label>31 Seconds or More</label>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> <!-- opaque container -->

      <div class="container col-xs-10 col-xs-push-1 quiz-question">
        <div class="form-group">
          <h3>Q4: Back Foot Balance</h3>
          <p><strong>How to Perform Stand on Back Leg</strong>
            <ol>
              <li>Look straight ahead. Keep your hands on your hips.</li>
              <li>Check the second hand on your watch and lift your forward leg off of the ground.  Do not touch or rest your raised leg upon your other standing leg.</li>
              <li>Stay standing on one leg as long as you can. Look straight ahead.</li>
              <li>When you lose balance, check how many seconds passed.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <div class="radio left-padding-30">
            <%= f.radio_button :bal04, '7'%><label>0 - 5 Seconds</label><br>
