        </div>
      </div> <!-- opaque container -->

      <div class="container col-xs-10 col-xs-push-1 quiz-question">
        <div class="form-group">
          <h3>Q5: Back Foot Balance, Motion</h3>
          <p><strong>How to Perform Stand on Back Leg with Movement</strong>
            <ol>
              <li>Take your golf posture with arms in front.</li>
              <li>Lift your forward leg off of the ground without touching or resting your raised leg upon your other standing leg.</li>
              <li>Once you have lifted your leg, check the second hand on your watch.</li>
              <li>Now slowly turn your forward arm in and let your hips turn, then slowly return  back to your original position</li>
              <li>Do this several times stay standing on one leg as long as you can. Look straight ahead.</li>
              <li>When you lose balance, check how many seconds passed after you add movement.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <div class="radio left-padding-30">
