            <%= f.radio_button :bal05, '1'%><label>31 Seconds or More</label>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> <!-- opaque container -->

      <div class="container col-xs-10 col-xs-push-1 quiz-question">
        <div class="form-group">
          <h3>Q6: Back Foot Balance, Eyes Closed</h3>
          <p><strong>How to Perform the Single Leg Balance Test, Eyes Closed</strong>
            <ol>
              <li>Stand tall with arms down by (but not touching) your sides.</li>
              <li>Elevate your forward leg until the thigh is parallel with the ground.</li>
              <li>Once stable, look at the second hand on your watch, then close your eyes and see how long you can maintain balance.</li>
              <li>Any re-positioning of the foot is considered a loss of balance. When you lose your balance, open your eyes and see how many seconds passed.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
          <div class="radio left-padding-30">
